        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-14 23:08:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI wonder if an mdt_write_allow() is needed in the same error path to deal with the similarly dangling mdt_write_deny().  But this fix looks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0d57d201e02bfdc18e31574bc1f3a4eb93657a80",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-15 00:11:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nGood catch, Chris!\n\n$ touch foo # create file\n$ chmod 400 foo\n$ ./foo # mot_writecount is now -1\n$ ./foo # mot_writecount is now -2\n$ ./foo # mot_writecount is now -3\n$ echo > foo \n-bash: foo: Text file busy\n$ chmod 600 foo\n$ echo > foo \n-bash: foo: Text file busy\n\nSame issue, but from a different angle.\n\nI'll update the patch to account for both cases, write and exec.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a136e56010bc7c9ab6b8dae2afd163764b8bc61c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-15 00:15:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nOn second thought, I'll add the exec case in a second patch. Since this is more or less correct as is, no re-reviewing is needed, and this can (hopefully) land more quickly.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
